.TH DATE 1 "2025" "Nightingale" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
date \- print or set the system date and time
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B date
.SH DESCRIPTION
Display the current date and time.
.PP
The output shows the current system time in a human-readable format.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B date
Display the current date and time.
.SH NOTES
The Nightingale date command:
.IP \(bu 3
Does not support format strings
.IP \(bu
Does not support setting the system time
.IP \(bu
Always displays time in UTC
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR btime (2),
.BR xtime (2),
.BR strftime (3)
